Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat
oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Place @black beans{1%unit} and their liquid, @butter{1%tbsp}, a pinch of
@salt{pinch}, and @pepper{} in one #oven-ready aluminum tray{} (for 4, divide
ingredients evenly between two trays, using 1 TBSP butter and a pinch of salt for
each tray).

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce}(dry) dry with #paper towels{}. Season all over with
@fajita spice blend{1%tablespoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Top bean mixture with
chicken. Drizzle with @olive oil{}.

In remaining oven-ready aluminum tray, combine @white rice{3/4%cup}, @Tex-Mex
paste{1}, @chicken stock concentrate{1%unit}, @water{1 1/4%cups}, @butter{1%tbsp},
and @sugar{1/2%tsp} (for 4 servings, divide ingredients evenly between remaining
two trays, using 1 1/4 cups water, 1 TBSP butter, and 1/2 tsp sugar for each
tray). Stir to combine. Season lightly with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Cover #oven-ready trays{} tightly with #aluminum foil{}. Place trays side by side
on top rack and bake until chicken is cooked through and rice is tender,
~{30-35%minutes}.

> For 4 servings, place rice on top rack and chicken on middle rack.

> Placing trays on a baking sheet makes transferring to the oven easier!

Meanwhile, pick @cilantro{1/4%ounce} leaves from stems.

Carefully remove aluminum foil from oven-ready trays (watch out for steam!).

Transfer chicken to a #cutting board{}. Let rest ~{5%minutes}, then slice
crosswise. Gently fluff rice with a #fork{}.

Divide chicken, beans, and rice between plates in separate sections. Drizzle
everything with @sour cream{3%tablespoon}; sprinkle with cilantro. Serve.

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.